    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="594"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.48/297</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1917</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>913. Your 573, 11th. General Polish Relief Committee writes that Committee
                    extends activity not only to Polish territory occupied by Germany and Austria
                    but also to various districts in Russia in which are numerous Polish refugees,
                    about one million persons, their needs enormous and daily growing. Committee
                    sends funds to local committees composed of persons of confidence. To present
                    date Committee has despatched to Russia over 938,000 francs. It is in constant
                    communication with these committees and can send funds reserved by American Red
                    Cross, of which funds it <pb facs="0585" n="501" xml:id="pg_501"/> will render
                    strict account. Expresses to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName>
                    hearty thanks for support by American Red Cross of objects of Committee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
